CREATE TABLE doctors (doctor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), specialization VARCHAR(50), hospital_id INT, experience_years INT, contact_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE medications (medication_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, medication_name VARCHAR(50), dosage VARCHAR(20), frequency VARCHAR(20), start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>UPSERT INTO patients (patient_id, name, age, gender, diagnosis, admission_date, discharge_date) VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 30, 'Male', 'Fever', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-10') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE name = VALUES(name), age = VALUES(age), gender = VALUES(gender), diagnosis = VALUES(diagnosis), admission_date = VALUES(admission_date), discharge_date = VALUES(discharge_date);</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE patients (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), diagnosis VARCHAR(100), admission_date DATE, discharge_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE doctors (doctor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), specialization VARCHAR(50), hospital_id INT, experience_years INT, contact_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE medications (medication_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, medication_name VARCHAR(50), dosage VARCHAR(20), frequency VARCHAR(20), start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE appointments (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, doctor_id INT, appointment_date DATE, time_slot VARCHAR(20), status VARCHAR(20))</t><s>UPSERT INTO patients (patient_id, name, age, gender, diagnosis, admission_date, discharge_date) VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 30, 'Male', 'Fever', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-10') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE name = VALUES(name), age = VALUES(age), gender = VALUES(gender), diagnosis = VALUES(diagnosis), admission_date = VALUES(admission_date), discharge_date = VALUES(discharge_date);</s>

CREATE TABLE medications (medication_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, medication_name VARCHAR(50), dosage VARCHAR(20), frequency VARCHAR(20), start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>upsert into patients (patient_id, name, age, gender, diagnosis, admission_date, discharge_date) values (1, 'john doe', 30, 'male', 'fever', '2023-01-05', '2023-01-10') on duplicate key update name = values(name), age = values(age), gender = values(gender), diagnosis = values(diagnosis), admission_date = values(admission_date), discharge_date = values(discharge_date);</s>

CREATE TABLE doctors (doctor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), specialization VARCHAR(50), hospital_id INT, experience_years INT, contact_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE appointments (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, doctor_id INT, appointment_date DATE, time_slot VARCHAR(20), status VARCHAR(20))</t><s>upsert into doctors (doctor_id, name, specialization, hospital_id, experience_years, contact_number) values (1, 'dr. smith', 'cardiology', 1234, 10, '123-456-7890') on duplicate key update name = values(name), specialization = values(specialization), hospital_id = values(hospital_id), experience_years = values(experience_years), contact_number = values(contact_number);</s>

CREATE TABLE appointments (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, doctor_id INT, appointment_date DATE, time_slot VARCHAR(20), status VARCHAR(20))</t><s>upsert into doctors (doctor_id, name, specialization, hospital_id, experience_years, contact_number) values (1, 'dr. smith', 'cardiology', 1234, 10, '123-456-7890') on duplicate key update name = values(name), specialization = values(specialization), hospital_id = values(hospital_id), experience_years = values(experience_years), contact_number = values(contact_number);</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE medications (medication_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, medication_name VARCHAR(50), dosage VARCHAR(20), frequency VARCHAR(20), start_date DATE, end_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE appointments (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, doctor_id INT, appointment_date DATE, time_slot VARCHAR(20), status VARCHAR(20))

CREATE TABLE doctors (doctor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), specialization VARCHAR(50), hospital_id INT, experience_years INT, contact_number VARCHAR(15))</t><s>UPSERT INTO doctors (doctor_id, name, specialization, hospital_id, experience_years, contact_number) VALUES (1, 'Dr. Smith', 'Cardiology', 1234, 10, '123-456-7890') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE name = VALUES(name), specialization = VALUES(specialization), hospital_id = VALUES(hospital_id), experience_years = VALUES(experience_years), contact_number = VALUES(contact_number);</s>

CREATE TABLE patients (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), diagnosis VARCHAR(100), admission_date DATE, discharge_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE medications (medication_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, medication_name VARCHAR(50), dosage VARCHAR(20), frequency VARCHAR(20), start_date DATE, end_date DATE)</t><s>upsert into appointments (appointment_id, patient_id, doctor_id, appointment_date, time_slot, status) values (1, 1, 1, '2023-01-15', '10:00 am - 11:00 am', 'confirmed') on duplicate key update patient_id = values(patient_id), doctor_id = values(doctor_id), appointment_date = values(appointment_date), time_slot = values(time_slot), status = values(status);</s>

CREATE TABLE patients (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), age INT, gender VARCHAR(10), diagnosis VARCHAR(100), admission_date DATE, discharge_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE doctors (doctor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, name VARCHAR(50), specialization VARCHAR(50), hospital_id INT, experience_years INT, contact_number VARCHAR(15))</t><s>UPSERT INTO appointments (appointment_id, patient_id, doctor_id, appointment_date, time_slot, status) VALUES (1, 1, 1, '2023-01-15', '10:00 AM - 11:00 AM', 'Confirmed') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE patient_id = VALUES(patient_id), doctor_id = VALUES(doctor_id), appointment_date = VALUES(appointment_date), time_slot = VALUES(time_slot), status = VALUES(status);</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) VALUES (1, 'Healthcare Provider 1', 'Type A', '123 Provider St', '123-456-7890') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE provider_name = 'Updated Provider 1', provider_type = 'Type B', address = '456 Provider St', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) VALUES (1, 'Healthcare Provider 1', 'Type A', '123 Provider St', '123-456-7890') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE provider_name = 'Updated Provider 1', provider_type = 'Type B', address = '456 Provider St', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))</t><s>upsert into healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) values (1, 'healthcare provider 1', 'type a', '123 provider st', '123-456-7890') on duplicate key update provider_name = 'updated provider 1', provider_type = 'type b', address = '456 provider st', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

<t>CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) VALUES (1, 'Healthcare Provider 1', 'Type A', '123 Provider St', '123-456-7890') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE provider_name = 'Updated Provider 1', provider_type = 'Type B', address = '456 Provider St', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><s>upsert into healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) values (1, 'healthcare provider 1', 'type a', '123 provider st', '123-456-7890') on duplicate key update provider_name = 'updated provider 1', provider_type = 'type b', address = '456 provider st', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) VALUES (1, 'Healthcare Provider 1', 'Type A', '123 Provider St', '123-456-7890') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE provider_name = 'Updated Provider 1', provider_type = 'Type B', address = '456 Provider St', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))</t><s>upsert into healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) values (1, 'healthcare provider 1', 'type a', '123 provider st', '123-456-7890') on duplicate key update provider_name = 'updated provider 1', provider_type = 'type b', address = '456 provider st', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO healthcare_provider (provider_id, provider_name, provider_type, address, phone_number) VALUES (1, 'Healthcare Provider 1', 'Type A', '123 Provider St', '123-456-7890') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE provider_name = 'Updated Provider 1', provider_type = 'Type B', address = '456 Provider St', phone_number = '111-222-3333';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))</t><s>upsert into patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) values (1, 'john doe', 'male', '1990-01-01', '123 patient st', '555-555-5555') on duplicate key update patient_name = 'updated john doe', patient_gender = 'female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 patient st', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>upsert into patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) values (1, 'john doe', 'male', '1990-01-01', '123 patient st', '555-555-5555') on duplicate key update patient_name = 'updated john doe', patient_gender = 'female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 patient st', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>upsert into patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) values (1, 'john doe', 'male', '1990-01-01', '123 patient st', '555-555-5555') on duplicate key update patient_name = 'updated john doe', patient_gender = 'female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 patient st', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>upsert into patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) values (1, 'john doe', 'male', '1990-01-01', '123 patient st', '555-555-5555') on duplicate key update patient_name = 'updated john doe', patient_gender = 'female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 patient st', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><s>upsert into patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) values (1, 'john doe', 'male', '1990-01-01', '123 patient st', '555-555-5555') on duplicate key update patient_name = 'updated john doe', patient_gender = 'female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 patient st', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 'Male', '1990-01-01', '123 Patient St', '555-555-5555') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE patient_name = 'Updated John Doe', patient_gender = 'Female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 Patient St', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><s>UPSERT INTO patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 'Male', '1990-01-01', '123 Patient St', '555-555-5555') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE patient_name = 'Updated John Doe', patient_gender = 'Female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 Patient St', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))</t><s>UPSERT INTO patient (patient_id, patient_name, patient_gender, patient_dob, patient_address, patient_phone) VALUES (1, 'John Doe', 'Male', '1990-01-01', '123 Patient St', '555-555-5555') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE patient_name = 'Updated John Doe', patient_gender = 'Female', patient_dob = '1991-01-01', patient_address = '456 Patient St', patient_phone = '999-999-9999';</s>
<t>CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))</t><s>UPSERT INTO appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) VALUES (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'General Checkup', 'Scheduled') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'Follow-up', appointment_status = 'Confirmed';</s>

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))</t><s>upsert into appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) values (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'general checkup', 'scheduled') on duplicate key update appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'follow-up', appointment_status = 'confirmed';</s>

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>upsert into appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) values (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'general checkup', 'scheduled') on duplicate key update appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'follow-up', appointment_status = 'confirmed';</s>

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))</t><s>UPSERT INTO appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) VALUES (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'General Checkup', 'Scheduled') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'Follow-up', appointment_status = 'Confirmed';</s>

CREATE TABLE insurance (insurance_id INT PRIMARY KEY, insurance_name VARCHAR(50), insurance_type VARCHAR(20), provider_id INT, start_date DATE, end_date DATE, FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>upsert into appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) values (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'general checkup', 'scheduled') on duplicate key update appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'follow-up', appointment_status = 'confirmed';</s>

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE medical_record (record_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, record_date DATETIME, diagnosis VARCHAR(100), prescription TEXT, FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>UPSERT INTO appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) VALUES (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'General Checkup', 'Scheduled') ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'Follow-up', appointment_status = 'Confirmed';</s>

CREATE TABLE patient (patient_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_name VARCHAR(50), patient_gender VARCHAR(10), patient_dob DATE, patient_address VARCHAR(100), patient_phone VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE healthcare_provider (provider_id INT PRIMARY KEY, provider_name VARCHAR(50), provider_type VARCHAR(50), address VARCHAR(100), phone_number VARCHAR(15))

CREATE TABLE appointment (appointment_id INT PRIMARY KEY, patient_id INT, provider_id INT, appointment_date DATETIME, appointment_type VARCHAR(20), appointment_status VARCHAR(20), FOREIGN KEY (patient_id) REFERENCES patient(patient_id), FOREIGN KEY (provider_id) REFERENCES healthcare_provider(provider_id))</t><s>upsert into appointment (appointment_id, patient_id, provider_id, appointment_date, appointment_type, appointment_status) values (1, 1, 1, '2022-01-01 10:00:00', 'general checkup', 'scheduled') on duplicate key update appointment_date = '2022-02-01 11:00:00', appointment_type = 'follow-up', appointment_status = 'confirmed';</s>
